  "text": "Nevertheless, for health communication and health policy scholars, such uncontrolled exposure to information on sensitive products like drugs, genetic testing and innovative medical interventions are cause for concerns, raising social and ethical issues [CITATION_1] . Several studies on direct-toconsumer online advertising and sale in such areas concluded that it can threaten information privacy, challenge equitable and safe access to healthcare, increase exposure to unreliable and biased information [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] , impact negatively the patient/physician relationship [CITATION_6] Racine et al., 2008) , corrupt the physician/ industry relationship, and increase overall spending in medical care [CITATION_7] .",
